T1	Intervention 136 365;366 630	NCX-4016 is a nitric oxide-releasing derivative of aspirin with antiplatelet activity. The aim of this study was to investigate the effect of NCX-4016 on gastrointestinal mucosa and platelet functions in healthy human volunteers. METHODS This was a parallel-group, double-blind, placebo-controlled study. Forty healthy subjects were randomly allocated to receive 7 days of treatment with NCX-4016 (400 and 800 mg twice daily), equimolar doses of aspirin (200 and 420 mg twice daily), or placebo
